Claims WHAT IS CLAIMED:  1) A method for performing a transaction, the method including using a system  including a payee client device, a payer client device and at least one payment processing device and wherein the method includes:  a) in an offline mode:  i) having the payee and payer client devices communicate to determine transaction details including at least a transaction amount;  ii) in a payer payment application executed by the payer client device:  (1) generating a transaction request including request transaction details indicative of at least the transaction amount;  (2) storing the transaction request; and,  (3) updating, in a secured manner, a payer available funds amount at least partially in accordance with the transaction amount; and, iii) in a payee payment application executed by the payee client device:  (1) generating a transaction confirmation including confirmation transaction details indicative of at least the transaction amount;  (2) storing the transaction confirmation; and,  (3) updating, in a secured manner, a payee available funds amount at least partially in accordance with the transaction amount; and, b) in an online mode:  i) in the payer payment application, providing the transaction request to at least one payment processing device;  ii) in the payee payment application, providing the transaction confirmation to the at least one payment processing device; and,  iii) having the at least one payment processing device:  (1) compare the request transaction details and confirmation transaction details; and  (2) causing the transaction to be selectively performed depending on  results of the comparison.  2) A method according to claim 1, wherein the method includes:  a) in the offline mode, in the payer payment application:  i) encrypting the transaction request; and,  ii) storing the encrypted transaction request; and,  b) in the online mode: 

 i) in the payer payment application, providing the encrypted transaction request to the at least one payment processing device;  ii) in the at least one payment processing device, decrypting the transaction request to determine the request transaction details.  3) A method according to claim 1 or claim 2, wherein the method includes:  a) in the offline mode, in the payee payment application:  i) encrypting the transaction confirmation; and,  ii) storing the encrypted transaction confirmation; and,  b) in the online mode:  i) in the payee payment application, providing the encrypted transaction confirmation to the at least one payment processing device;  ii) in the at least one payment processing device, decrypting the transaction confirmation to determine the confirmation transaction details.4) A method according to any one of the claims 1 to 3, wherein the method includes: a) in the payer payment application, storing the transaction request until at least one of:  i) an online mode is commenced by establishing communication with the at least one payment processing device; and,  ii) a transaction query is received from the at least one payment processing device; and,  b) in the payee payment application, storing the transaction confirmation until at least one of:  i) an online mode is commenced by establishing communication with the at least one payment processing device; and,  ii) a transaction query is received from the at least one payment processing device.  5) A method according to any one of the claims 1 to 4, wherein the method includes, in the payer payment application, deterrnining transaction details including the transaction amount in accordance with user input commands.  6) A method according to any one of the claims 1 to 5, wherein the method includes establishing a short range wireless communications channel between the payee and payer client devices.  7) A method according to claim 6, wherein the method includes establishing a  communications channel between the payee and payer client devices by: 

 a) having the payer and payee client device determine respective authorisation codes;  b) comparing the authorisation codes; and,  c) establishing the communications channel if the authorisation codes match. 8) A method according to claim 7, wherein the method includes:  a) having one of the client devices generate and display the authorisation code; and,  b) having a user enter the authorisation code via the other user client device.9) A method according to any one of the claims 6 to 8, wherein the method includes: a) in the payer payment application, providing a transaction message to the payee client device via the communications channel, the transaction message including message transaction details including at least the transaction amount; and,  b) in the payee payment application, using the transaction message to generate the transaction confirmation.  10) A method according to any one of the claims 1 to 9, wherein the method includes: a) in the offline mode, establishing a shared secret, the shared secret being shared by the payer and payee payment applications; and,  b) in the online mode and in the at least one payment processing device, using the shared secret to authorise the transaction.  11) A method according to claim 10, wherein the method includes, in the at least one payment processing device:  a) determining an indication of the shared secret from each of the transaction request and the transaction confirmation; and,  b) using each indication of the shared secret to authorise the transaction.  12) A method according to claim 10 or claim 11, wherein the shared secret includes at least one of:  a) a secret key;  b) a signature;  c) a signature generated using a private key of a public/private key pair; and, d) a signature generated using transaction details.  13) A method according to any one of the claims 1 to 12, wherein the method  includes, in the payer payment processing application:  a) determining if a number of offline transactions will exceed a limit; and, 

 b) causing the transaction to be selectively performed depending on results of the determination.  14) A method according to any one of the claims 1 to 13, wherein the method  includes, in the payer payment application:  a) determining the transaction amount;  b) comparing the transaction amount to a payer available funds amount; and, c) causing the transaction to be selectively performed depending on results of the comparison.  15) A method according to any one of the claims 1 to 14, wherein the method  includes, in the payer payment application:  a) determining payer authentication information;  b) attempting to authenticate the payer using the payer authentication  information; and,  c) causing the transaction to be selectively performed depending on results of the attempt.  16) A method according to claim 15, wherein the payer authentication information includes at least one of:  a) payer biometric information determined using a biometric reader; and, b) a PIN determined using payer input commands provided via an input device. 17) A method according to any one of the claims 1 to 16, wherein the method  includes, in the at least one payment processing device and in the online mode, at least one of:  a) updating a payee account balance in a payee account in accordance with â¢ performed transaction; and,  b) updating a payer account balance in a payer account in accordance with  performed transaction. 18) A method according to any one of the claims 1 to 17, wherein the request  transaction details include at least one of:  a) the transaction amount;  b) a payer funds amount;  c) a transaction account identifier;  d) a transaction identifier;  e) a transaction time;  f) a transaction date; 

 g) a payer identifier;  h) a payee identifier;  i) a secret key;  j) information encrypted using a secret key; and,  k) a signature generated using a private key of a payer public/private key pair.19) A method according to any one of the claims 1 to 18, wherein the confirmation transaction details include:  a) the transaction amount;  b) a transaction account identifier;  c) a transaction identifier;  d) a transaction time;  e) a transaction date;  f) a payer identifier;  g) a payee identifier;  h) a secret key;  i) information encrypted using a secret key; and,  j) a signature generated using a private key of a payer public/private key pair.20) A method according to claim 9, wherein the message transaction details include at least one of:  a) the transaction amount;  b) a transaction identifier;  c) a transaction time;  d) a transaction date;  e) a payer identifier;  f) a secret key; and,  g) a signature generated using a private key of a payer public/private key pair.21) A method according to any one of the claims 1 to 20, wherein the method  includes:  a) in the offline mode:  i) establishing a communications channel between the payee and payer client devices;  ii) in a payer payment application executed by the payer client device:  (1) determining a transaction amount; 

 (2) selectively confirming if the transaction can proceed based on the transaction amount and a payer available funds amount;  (3) in response to a successful confirmation:  (a) providing a transaction message to the payee client device via the communications channel, the transaction message including message transaction details including at least the transaction amount;  (b) generating the transaction request;  (c) encrypting the transaction request with a public key of at least one payment processing device public/private key pair;  (d) storing the encrypted transaction request; and,  (e) updating the payer available funds amount;  iii) in a payee payment application executed by the payee client device: (1) receiving the transaction message; and, (2) updating a payee available funds amount at least in part in accordance with the transaction amount; (3) generate the transaction confirmation; (4) encrypt the transaction confirmation with a public key of at least one payment processing device public/private key pair; and, (5) store the encrypted transaction confirmation; and, b) in an online mode: i) in the payer payment application, providing the encrypted transaction request to the at least one payment processing device; ii) in the payee payment application, providing the encrypted transaction confirmation to the at least one payment processing device; iii) in the at least one payment processing device: (1) decrypting the transaction request with a private key of at least one payment processing device public/private key pair to determine the request transaction details; (2) decrypting the transaction confirmation with the private key of at least one payment processing device public/private key pair to determine the confirmation transaction details; (3) comparing the confirmation and request transaction details; and, 

 (4) selectively processing the transaction in accordance with results of the comparison. 22) A method for performing a transaction, the method including, in a payer client device: a) in an offline mode: i) communicating with a payee client device to determine transaction details including at least a transaction amount; ii) in a payer payment application: (1) generating a transaction request including request transaction details indicative of at least the transaction amount; (2) updating a payer available funds amount at least partially in accordance with the transaction amount; and, b) in an online mode providing the transaction request to at least one payment processing device, the at least one payment processing device causing the transaction to be selectively performed using the request transaction details. 23) A method for performing a transaction, the method including, in a payee client device: a) in an offline mode: i) communicating with a payer client device to determine transaction details including at least a transaction amount; ii) in a payee payment application: (1) generating a transaction confirmation including confirmation transaction details indicative of at least the transaction amount; (2) updating a payee available funds amount at least partially in accordance with the transaction amount; and, b) in an online mode providing the transaction confirmation to at least one payment processing device, the at least one payment processing device causing the transaction to be selectively performed using the confirmation transaction details. 24) A method for performing a transaction, the method including, in at least one payment processing device and in an online mode: a) receiving, from a payer payment application, a transaction request including request transaction details indicative of at least a transaction amount; 

